      <h1>Analyzing Lactose Intolerance with Ancient DNA</h1>
      <p>
        It is time to dive into some ancient DNA! You now have an understanding
        of what SNPs are. We will be looking at 5 lactose intolerance-related
        SNPs in ancient humans. The 5 SNPs are shown in the table below. These
        SNPs are strongly associated with lactase persistence.
      </p>

      <table class="table table-bordered">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>SNP</th>
            <th>Alternative Name</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>rs4954490</td>
            <td>−13495:C>T</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>rs41525747</td>
